# Dialog render (layout builder)

Read `.cursor/AGENTS.md` and `skills/generate-dialog-json/SKILL.md` before generating dialog JSON.

## Mode detection

- **Composed**: `children` has `dialog-trigger` or `dialog-content` → legacy props ignored.
- **Legacy**: use `trigger`, `title`, `description`, `children` (body), `footer`.

## JSON rules

- Root: `type: "dialog"`. Slots: `dialog-trigger`, `dialog-content`, `dialog-header`, `dialog-title`, `dialog-description`, `dialog-footer`.
- `dialog-title` / `dialog-description`: required `text`.
- `showCloseButton` on legacy dialog / `dialog-content` defaults `true`; on `dialog-footer` defaults `false`.
- Composed order: `dialog-trigger` then `dialog-content` (header/body/footer inside content).
- Wrapper div receives root `className` / `style`.

## Pitfalls

- Missing trigger — legacy needs `trigger` array; composed needs `dialog-trigger` with button child.
- Mixing legacy `trigger` with composed slots — pick one mode.
- `label` on dialog-title — use `text`.
